File Structure
--------------
* main.py - Starts program
* app.py - Main Kivy App
* connection.py - Interface to SSH and SFTP server
* term_em.py - Terminal emulator interface
* gui/
    * main_window.py - Master window
        * master_tab.py - Single tab for unique connection
            * loader.py - Tab loading widget
            * login.py - Login widget
            * connection_view.py - Connected tab: holds terminal and file explorer
                * terminal.py - Terminal Widget
                * fileexplorer.py - File Explorer Widget

Interface
---------
Connection(username):
    attempt_connection:
        returns True if connection successful
        returns False is unable to authenticate
    attempt_login(username, password):
        returns True if login (and thus connection) successful
        returns False if unable to authenticate
    send_ssh_bytes(bytes)
    has_ssh_data():
        returns True if there is buffered data
        returns False otherwise
    receive_ssh_data():
        returns buffered received data

MasterTab:
    give_credentials:
        receive credentials from child Login

Login:
    init(error_message?):
        Display error_message (if exists) on startup

Project Setup Guide
-------------------
To create your virtual environment, from project directory:
    pipenv install

To select the virtual environment in PyCharm:
    Preferences
    Project: SEASide
    Project Interpreter
    Project Interpreter: Show all
    +: Add local
    Existing environment
    Find and select your pipenv virtual environment

When you want to push you changes to GitHub:
    VCS -> Commit
    VCS -> Git -> Fetch
    On the bottom-right of the window:
        Git
        Remote Branches: origin/master -> Merge
    VCS -> Git -> Push

To run through PyCharm:
    Select empty selector on top right
    Edit Configurations
    + -> Python
        Name: SEASide
        Script path: main.py
        Working directory: set to main repository directory